            <q>in a manner which maintains the natural environment",</q>
            are gentle words that balance the word "exploitation", which my noble friend mentioned. She gave an interpretation of what "exploitation" could mean. It is interesting that my dictionary&#x2014;I, too, looked it up because it is a harsh word&#x2014;defines it as:
            <q>to use or develop for one's own ends or to take advantage of".</q>
            That interpretation is not as nice, but if we add the words,
            <q>in a manner which maintains the natural environment",</q>
            that would counterbalance the wording. I cannot imagine that those eight words would make such an enormous difference to the Bill.
          </p>
