            The nonsense is that it would be possible for there to be a wind turbine installation that covered an area partly adjacent to England and partly adjacent to Scotland. It would then be possible to make an Order in Council which classified&#x2014;this is a very silly example&#x2014;throwing stones as a criminal activity. if Scottish Ministers did not agree, that activity would not be criminal in that part of the installation which was in Scottish waters.</p><p>
            Perhaps the Minister will enlighten me as to whether pursuit of an offender from English to Scottish waters would be allowed&#x2014;or is that something else that, having been devolved, Scottish Ministers can prevent?
